@node INFO "INFO"
This guide will let you EXTRACT selected archives from the cd's, to ram:
Each archive is given a brief description, to let you know what it is.

This guide only covers the @{b}ARCHIVES@{ub} from the CD's, There is also a
selection of @{b}ready to use@{ub} software on the CD's, but I didn't feel
a guide was important for those files.

The only reason this guide was written, was because I didn't like the
archive lister which was included on the CD.  This guide can happily sit on
your hard drive, and will let you view the @{b}archived@{ub} contents of
both CD's, without having them in your CD Drive.

This Guide was written by @{" Martin Walters " link ME} and was originally
designed for my own use, the only reason I've made it available to you is
the fact that I wanted to upload something to the Aminet.

I make no promises that this guide will be of any use to you whatsoever,
and take no responsibility for anything bad that may happen as a result of
using this guide (death of your computer or loss of data for example).

On the other hand, I take full credit for anything good that may arise from
the use of this guide (World peace, increased sex drive etc, etc).

I have absolutely no connection with PDSOFT, for info on their range of
products you should contact them.

@{" FRONT PAGE " link MAIN}
@endnode

@node ME "Martin Walters -- EXCALIBVRS DOMAIN 1999"

This guide was written for my own personal use, and I like it.  It is the
first time I have EVER done anything productive with my Amiga, and I hope
you like it and/or find it useful.

It would make my day if I got a message from someone who is using this
guide, so please write (even if it's only to tell me that you don't like
it)

you can contact me in the following ways:

                        @{b}EMAIL - xcalibvr@yahoo.com@{ub}
                    @{b}EMAIL - xcalibvr@domain.karoo.co.uk@{ub}
                                    OR
                           @{b}FIDONET - 2:2502/7.6@{ub}

This guide is released under the concept of EVERYWARE, 'cos that's where I
want it to go :)


